               <head>Miscellaneous works on Sufism, 5 items (a-e)</head>
               <msContents class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008112367 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807">
                  <summary>Miscellaneous collection of works on Sufism, and the spiritual genealogies of <persName key="person_f7598" role="subject">Shaykh Pīr Muḥammad</persName> traced through three Sufi traditions. Volume not dated. Scribal nastaʿlīq and shikastah āmīz. Annotations in margins. Stamped foliation. Lacking original binding. Leather binding, damaged, labels. Folios mostly bound; severely cropped, wormholes, later repairs. Condition fragile. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1012-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="41v">ff. 1r-41v</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item a. Catalogued as no. 1251 by Storey, Arabic MSS in IOL, vol. ii (1930). </p>
                        <p>Arabic treatise, conventionally titled <title>Ādāb al-murīdīn</title>, epitomising Ṣūfī doctrine, by <persName key="viaf_101053660" role="aut">Abū al-Najīb ʿAbd al-Qāhir ibn ʿAbd Allāh al-Suhravardī</persName> (d. 563/1168). 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. 
</p>
                        <p>The colophon (f. 41v) concludes with the Persian rubāʿīyāt ascribed to <persName key="person_f7424" role="oth">Mullā Mukhtārī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Persian annotations in margin. 
</p>
                        <p>Coarse nastaʿlīq. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="per">Arabic and Persian</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22178">Ādāb al-murīdīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22178">آداب المريدين</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="viaf_101053660">Abū al-Najīb ʿAbd al-Qāhir ibn ʿAbd Allāh al-Suhravardī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="viaf_101053660">ابو النّجيب عبد القاهر ابن عبد الله السّهروردى</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1012-item2">
                     <locus from="42v" to="43r">ff. 42v-43r</locus>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22179">Shajarah-'i pīrān-i Qādirīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22179">شجرهٴ پيران قادريّه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item b. </p>
                        <p>Brief treatise listing in the spiritual genealogy of <orgName>Qādirī</orgName> Ṣūfī leaders, the latest being <persName key="person_f7598" role="subject">Shaykh Pīr Muḥammad</persName> traced back via <persName key="person_f7184" role="subject">Imām Mūsá al-Kāẓim</persName> to the Khalīfah and <persName key="viaf_34436377" role="subject">Imām ʿAlī ibn Abū Ṭālib</persName> and ultimately the <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The author or authority for the tradition is not named. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                        <p>Coarse shikastah āmīz. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1012-item3">
                     <locus from="43v" to="44r">ff. 43v-44r</locus>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item c. </p>
                        <p>Brief treatise listing in the spiritual genealogy of <orgName>Chishtī</orgName> Ṣūfī leaders, the latest being <persName key="person_f7598" role="subject">Shaykh Pīr Muḥammad</persName> traced back via <persName key="viaf_90045570" role="subject">Ḥasan Baṣrī</persName> and <persName key="viaf_34436377" role="subject">Imām ʿAlī ibn Abū Ṭālib</persName> and ultimately the <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The author or authority for the tradition is not named. 
</p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                        <p>Coarse shikastah āmīz. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22180">Shajarah-'i pīrān-i Chisht ahl-i bihisht</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22180">شجرهٴ پيران چشت اهل بهشت</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="4" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1012-item4">
                     <locus from="44v" to="45r">ff. 44v-45r</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item d. </p>
                        <p>Brief treatise listing in the spiritual genealogy of <orgName>Suhravardī</orgName> Ṣūfī leaders, the latest being <persName key="person_f7598" role="subject">Shaykh Pīr Muḥammad</persName> traced back via <persName key="viaf_90045570" role="subject">Ḥasan Baṣrī</persName> and <persName key="viaf_34436377" role="subject">Imām ʿAlī ibn Abū Ṭālib</persName> and ultimately the <persName key="viaf_97245226" role="subject">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>The author or authority for the tradition is not named. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22181">Shajarah-'i pīrān-i Suhravardī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22181">شجرهٴ پيران سهروردى</title>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="5" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1012-item5">
                     <locus from="45v" to="47v">ff. 45v-47v</locus>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian and Arabic</textLang>
                     <note>
                        <p>Item e. </p>
                        <p>Untitled treatise on the induction or bayʿah of novice men (f. 45v) and women (f. 46v) into the <orgName>Naqshbandī</orgName> Ṣūfī order, by an unnamed author. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Not dated at end. </p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
